CONFCLOUD-19389
{panel}


As a user, I want the option to copy a page without attachments so that I can get the structure of a page without old data.

My use case is meeting minutes where I want to copy/paste the previous minutes rather than start with an empty template.  When you copy a page, all attachments are also copied.  If I leave the attachments in place, the number of attachments steadily grows until I start getting timeout errors when copying.  If I delete the attachments after the copy, all users who are watching the space get a notification email for each deletion.  Both are bad choices.

h3. Summary

Add controls to the dynamic macro propertyPanel as (i.e.https://developer.atlassian.com/cloud/confluence/modules/macro-property-panel),  You should be able to add the UI components, however, handlers to the components are not binded properly:

{{atlassian-descriptor.json}}:

- Add the propertyPanel element to the macro and define a number of buttons.
{code}
"propertyPanel": {
    "url": "/hello-world",
    "controls": [
        {
            "type": "button",
            "label": {"value": "<img src='{{confluenceConnectHost}}/icons/size-property-button.png' style='width:20px;height:20px;margin-top:4px' />"},
            "key": "sizeButtonSmall"
        },
        {
            "type": "button",
            "label": {"value": "<img src='{{confluenceConnectHost}}/icons/size-property-button.png' style='width:16px;height:16px;margin-top:6px' />"},
            "key": "sizeButtonMedium"
        },
        {
            "type": "button",
            "label": {"value": "<img src='{{confluenceConnectHost}}/icons/size-property-button.png' style='width:12px;height:12px;margin-top:8px' />"},
            "key": "sizeButtonLarge"
        },
        {
            "type": "button",
            "label": {"value": "Original"},
            "key": "sizeButtonOriginal"
        }
    ]
}
{code}

- The buttons appear on the macro panel, and properties-panel.html loads as expected.

- In your html, I include all.js and execute {{onMacroPropertyPanelEvent}} to associate event handlers to the buttons.  Add debugger statements to see if the various actions are being executed.  Here is the code:
{code}
<script type="text/javascript" src="{{baseUrl}}/atlassian-connect/all-debug.js" data-options="margin:false"></script>
<script type="text/javascript">
try {
    debugger;
    AP.require('confluence', function(confluence) {
       debugger;
       confluence.onMacroPropertyPanelEvent({
            "sizeButtonLarge-click.some.macro.property-panel": function () {
                debugger;
            },
            "sizeButtonMedium-click.some.macro.property-panel": function () {
                debugger;
            },
            "sizeButtonSmall-click.some.macro.property-panel": function () {
                debugger;
            }
       });
    });
    debugger;
} catch (err) {
    debugger;
}

</script>
{code}

Aside from the events not binded, the event handler names are not in the documentation.  The pages, and {{confluence.onMacroPropertyPanelEvent()}} executes without error, but the event functions do not execute when a button is clicked.

h3. Summary

Backspace deletes contents in other table cells, not only the one selected.

 
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Go to a page and add a table;
 # Add some text to the table;
 # Delete the text from a random cell;

h3. Expected Results
 * The selected text from the cell is removed.

h3. Actual
 * The selected text from the cell is removed, but the text from other cells is also removed.

h3. Summary  
* If more than 100 space's shortcuts are added to a specific space in Confluence, this space will face performance issues on loading its content.

h3. Steps to Reproduce 
# On a specific space, click on the *Edit* button on the bottom of the left sidebar;
# Click on *Add Shortcut*;
# Look for another space on the *Search* field;
# Click on *Insert* button;
# Repeat the process to add 100 spaces shortcuts;
# Click on the *Done* button.

h3. Expected Results  
* Space overview loads its content normally.

h3. Actual Results 
* The space overview takes a while to load its content, including the shortcuts.

h3.Workaround 
* Remove the shortcuts and add a link to the Space Directory on the overview page of the space.

